“𝐂𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐚 𝐑𝐞𝐬𝐮𝐦𝐞 𝐢𝐬 𝐍𝐨𝐭 𝐄𝐧𝐨𝐮𝐠𝐡 – 𝐂𝐡𝐞𝐜𝐤 𝐘𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐀𝐓𝐒 𝐒𝐜𝐨𝐫𝐞 & 𝐎𝐩𝐭𝐢𝐦𝐢𝐳𝐞 𝐋𝐢𝐧𝐤𝐞𝐝𝐈𝐧!”

In today’s competitive job market, just having a resume won’t help you stand out  𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐧𝐞𝐞𝐝 𝐚𝐧 𝐀𝐓𝐒-𝐨𝐩𝐭𝐢𝐦𝐢𝐳𝐞𝐝 𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐮𝐦𝐞!

📌 𝐖𝐡𝐚𝐭’𝐬 𝐀𝐓𝐒?
 Applicant Tracking Systems (ATS) are used by most companies to scan and filter resumes before they reach the hands of a recruiter.

Here’s the truth 👇

🔹 90%+ 𝐀𝐓𝐒 𝐒𝐜𝐨𝐫𝐞
 ✅ Your resume 𝘥𝘪𝘳𝘦𝘤𝘵𝘭𝘺 𝘭𝘢𝘯𝘥𝘴 in the recruiter’s hands.
 ✅ Shows you’ve perfectly matched keywords, role responsibilities, and format.
 ✅ High chance of getting shortlisted.

🔹 70% – 89% 𝐀𝐓𝐒 𝐒𝐜𝐨𝐫𝐞
 ⚠️ Moderate chance of getting noticed.
 ⚠️ Needs improvement in formatting, keyword usage, or alignment with the job description.

🔹 𝐁𝐞𝐥𝐨𝐰 70%
 🚫 Often filtered out before a human ever sees it.
 🚫 Missing relevant keywords, incorrect formatting, generic wording.

✅ 𝐓𝐢𝐩𝐬 𝐭𝐨 𝐈𝐦𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐯𝐞 𝐀𝐓𝐒 𝐒𝐜𝐨𝐫𝐞 & 𝐕𝐢𝐬𝐢𝐛𝐢𝐥𝐢𝐭𝐲:
 🔸 Tailor your resume to every job description.
 🔸 Use exact keywords and phrases from the JD.
 🔸 Avoid fancy templates – stick to clean formatting.
 🔸 Highlight measurable results, not just tasks.
 🔸 Use a proper title and skills section.
 🔸 Include tools, tech stacks, and certifications clearly.


💼 𝐁𝐮𝐭 𝐭𝐡𝐚𝐭’𝐬 𝐣𝐮𝐬𝐭 𝐇𝐀𝐋𝐅 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐠𝐚𝐦𝐞!

 𝐋𝐢𝐧𝐤𝐞𝐝𝐈𝐧 𝐎𝐩𝐭𝐢𝐦𝐢𝐳𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐢𝐬 𝐞𝐪𝐮𝐚𝐥𝐥𝐲 𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐨𝐫𝐭𝐚𝐧𝐭!
 🔹 Appears in recruiter searches.
 🔹 Helps build a strong digital presence.
 🔹 Showcases your skills, recommendations, and projects.
 🔹 Acts as a living resume + portfolio.
